commit.message: Make MaskAtom class derive from object.
Don't rely on docstrings to provide help messages.

Reimplement SyncedUnmaskFile class.

Now, instead of dirty comparing and sorting we're using a real live
class to keep the unmask file in sync. It operates directly on the mask
entries, marking those supposedly used within the unmask file.
Support checking repository existence through (reponame in f).
Improve the DiffmaskBlock comparison to make it work at all.
Include the COPYING file in distutils tarball.
Bump PV to 0.3.3.
Use match_to_list() when comparing a CPV against the mask entry.
Document the API.
Drop the trailing blank line in MaskMerge.
Drop MaskMerge.ProcessAll().
Ensure the trailing newline in MaskMerge(). Drop empty repos.
Restore the newline following the repo header.
Clean the mask parsing code up.

Drop the concept of MaskEntry.before.

It used to contain whitespace coming before the entry comment. There's
no real use for that information, especially that it was grabbed only
for the first mask entry and resulted in trouble when trying to separate
repo headers from entries.
Drop pointless join() on a string.

Clean the repo parsing code up a little.

This should make it more readable and maintainable. This should also fix
appending whitespace to the last entry of the previous repo.
Fix incorrect return statements in add() and delete().
Don't add leading whitespace as package entries.
Drop a unused var.
Drop the trailing newline from output file.
Require each mask entry to end with a newline.

Reduce whitespace mangling to minimum.

I'm temporarily reducing the whitespace mangling in diffmask to minimum.
This makes the repository headers are going to look worse than before
but newlines won't replicate any longer.

The newline-separators around repository headers are going to be readded
soon.
Prefer __file__ over argv[0] in setup.py.
Fix py3 compat in module loading fallback.
Introduce Atom() compatibility with portage-2.1.8.
Import os.path only when necessary.
Try to ensure a clean re-try at loading diffmask.cli.
Move most of core diffmask code to diffmask.cli.
Delay config loading until it's really necessary.
